n class=usertitle>LED ZEPPELIN</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/30/01 12:46:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sabbathfan333.homestead.com/files/images/lz-3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most Immersive RPG Ever??</span><hr size=1> In no particular order, and sorry for bumping an old thread <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Trad RPG</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Xenogears</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> My GOD this has the greatest story I've ever seen in a game, at least in my humble opinion.<br>I played this thing for massive amounts of time after I got it, pushing past 12 hours a day (thx winter break~). When I was done, I was completely clueless as to how much time had passed until I checked the clock <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Honorable Mention</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Final Fantasy Seven</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The first game I ever truly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> mastered</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as in finding every secret in, and I assure you I did <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Other RPG</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Final Fantasy Tactics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Pure ownage of a game. Top-notch storyline. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Baldur's Gate 2</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Excellent game, now if only I could get a better computer to run it on...<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Misc. Games</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Castlevania: Symphony of the Night</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I could sit and play this for an entire night and not feel tired...great, great game, can have nonstop action if you want it, or you can dip out and chill and enjoy the scenery for awhile. I'm still convinced I haven't found all the secrets <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rise of the Triad: Darkwar</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> WHY has no one else in the world but me heard of this game?! It was very good, came out in I think 1994 or 5. FPS, excellent graphics and level design for its day. Freaky end boss <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Movies</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Indiana Jones and the Raiders of the Lost Ark</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Clerks</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dogma</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Star Wars Trilogy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> No matter how many times I watch any of these, it's impossible to get tired of them.<br><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Books</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sword of Truth series</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> No Direction Home</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->(Bob Dylan biography <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Bram Stoker's Dracula</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dune series</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END